HEADWORD: Snift
<hw>Snift</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Snifted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Snifting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From <er>Sniff</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To snort.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Resentment
expressed by <xex>snifting</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To sniff; to snuff; to smell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It now appears that they were still <qex>snifing</qex> and
hankering after their old quarters.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snift</ent>⟦br⟧

